    <div class="tb-cmdintro">
      <h1>Command Reference</h1>
      <p>Every Tacklebox command, grouped by feature, with separate walkthroughs for players and officers. Commands run as Discord slash commands — type <code>/</code> in any channel the bot can see.</p>
    </div>

    <section id="party" class="tb-cmdsection">
      <div class="tb-cmdtitle"><h2>Party Manager</h2><code class="tb-slashchip">/party</code></div>
      <p class="tb-cmddesc">Connects a Google Sheet to Discord for party signups. Officers start a party from a sheet URL, players sign up for weapons/roles via buttons, and officers assign roles in the sheet and sync them back to Discord.</p>

      <div class="tb-cmdcard">
        <div class="tb-cmdcard-label">COMMANDS</div>
        <div class="tb-cmdrows">
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/party start &lt;url&gt;</code><span>Start a new party signup from a Google Sheet URL. Cap of 10 active parties per server; parties auto-expire after 10 days.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tb-flowgrid">
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-player">PLAYER FLOW</div>
          <ol>
            <li>Click <strong>Sign Up</strong>, select the weapon(s) you can play, add notes if needed (low spec, early leave). Written to the sheet automatically.</li>
            <li>Click Sign Up again any time to update your selections.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Un-Sign Up</strong> to remove your signup from the sheet and party.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>View Loadout</strong> after officers sync to see your assigned weapon and required equipment.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-officer">OFFICER FLOW</div>
          <ol>
            <li>Run <code>/party start &lt;sheet URL&gt;</code>. Pick a tab if the sheet has multiple.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Add Details</strong> for event title, UTC time, meeting place, gear, and description.</li>
            <li>Copy signups from Column A into Column F next to their assigned weapon (names must match exactly).</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Sync</strong> to pull Column F into the embed. Repeat as your roster changes.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>End Party</strong> to close signups and remove buttons. Sync/Details/End can be used by the starter or anyone with Manage Server.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>

      <details class="tb-details">
        <summary>Sheet setup &amp; column layout</summary>
        <div class="tb-details-body">
          <p>Copy the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1b-jZ0mVhxWnB1H5FfGaDvcJO2D9vmJLrg5mQcMthyeY/edit?gid=0#gid=0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sheet template</a> (File → Make a copy) and share it with the bot's service account — <code>tacklebox-bot@tacklebox-489703.iam.gserviceaccount.com</code> — as <strong>Editor</strong>.</p>
          <p><strong>A–C</strong> — Player signups, written automatically. Don't edit.</p>
          <p><strong>D</strong> — Role (Tank, Healer, DPS...). <strong>E</strong> — Weapon name, one per row.</p>
          <p><strong>F</strong> — Assignments. Paste player names exactly as they appear in Column A.</p>
          <p><strong>G+</strong> — Equipment loadout; header row names the slot, cells list required items. Shown to players via View Loadout.</p>
          <p>⚠️ Don't rearrange or delete columns A–F — the bot reads fixed column positions.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section id="loot" class="tb-cmdsection">
      <div class="tb-cmdtitle"><h2>Loot Split</h2><code class="tb-slashchip">/loot</code></div>
      <p class="tb-cmddesc">Splits loot silver evenly among party members. Start the split, members react to join, officers can adjust the player list, and the bot calculates each player's cut after repairs and guild tax.</p>

      <div class="tb-cmdcard">
        <div class="tb-cmdcard-label">COMMANDS</div>
        <div class="tb-cmdrows">
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/loot start</code><span>Start a new loot split message in the current channel. Optional: <code>voice_channel</code> for the Ping button, <code>tax_rate</code> to override the guild default.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode-admin">/admin set_default_tax</code><span>Admin only. Sets the guild's default tax rate (0–100%). Default is 35% if never set.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tb-flowgrid">
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-player">PLAYER FLOW</div>
          <ol>
            <li>React to the loot split embed with any emoji to join — one reaction counts, doesn't matter which emoji.</li>
            <li>If an officer excludes you, you won't appear on the payout checklist even if you reacted.</li>
            <li>If self-marking is enabled, click <strong>Mark Myself Paid</strong> once you're paid. Only works if you're unpaid and included.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-officer">OFFICER FLOW</div>
          <ol>
            <li>Run <code>/loot start</code>. The bot posts an embed; unique reactors are counted automatically.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Ping Voice Channel</strong> to @mention everyone in the selected voice channel.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Player Override</strong> (initiator only) to Add, Exclude, or Reset players — up to 40 per list, deduplicated against reactions.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Calculate</strong> and fill in Total Silver, Repair Cost, and Tax Rate (pre-filled with the guild default).</li>
            <li>Run <code>/admin set_default_tax &lt;0–100&gt;</code> to change the default used by Calculate.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>

      <details class="tb-details">
        <summary>Payout checklist, in detail</summary>
        <div class="tb-details-body">
          <p>After Calculate runs, the bot posts a checklist with three states: ❌ unpaid, ✅ paid directly, 💰 deposited into bank.</p>
          <p><strong>Marking paid</strong> — dropdowns below the checklist show only unpaid players; picking one marks them ✅. More than 25 unpaid adds more dropdowns.</p>
          <p><strong>Bank</strong> — opens a private panel to deposit unpaid players' cuts into <code>/bank</code>; Bank All covers everyone unpaid.</p>
          <p><strong>Reset</strong> — sends ✅/💰 players back to ❌; banked players have the split withdrawn from their balance.</p>
          <p>⚠️ The checklist only responds for <strong>1 hour</strong> after posting. Bank changes already made stay in <code>/bank</code> — use <code>/bank update</code> for manual corrections.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section id="regear" class="tb-cmdsection">
      <div class="tb-cmdtitle"><h2>Regear Timer</h2><code class="tb-slashchip">/regear</code></div>
      <p class="tb-cmddesc">Tracks gear reimbursements. Officers start a timer for a player, the player reacts to confirm they've collected their gear, and the bot notifies the officer to empty the chest — or marks it expired if time runs out.</p>

      <div class="tb-cmdcard">
        <div class="tb-cmdcard-label">COMMANDS</div>
        <div class="tb-cmdrows">
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/regear start &lt;user&gt; &lt;chest&gt;</code><span>e.g. <code>/regear start @Angler 3</code>. Each player can have up to 5 active timers.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode-admin">/admin set_reminder &lt;hours&gt;</code><span>Admin only. 1–168h, must be less than expiry. Default: 24h.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode-admin">/admin set_expiry &lt;hours&gt;</code><span>Admin only. 1–168h, must be greater than reminder. Default: 48h.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tb-flowgrid">
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-player">PLAYER FLOW</div>
          <ol>
            <li>The bot tags you with a message showing the chest number and how long you have to claim.</li>
            <li>React with ✅ once you've picked up your gear — on the original message or a reminder, either works.</li>
            <li>If you haven't reacted after the reminder window (default 24h), a follow-up reminder is sent.</li>
            <li>If the timer expires before you react, it's marked expired — reach out to the officer directly.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-officer">OFFICER FLOW</div>
          <ol>
            <li>Run <code>/regear start &lt;@player&gt; &lt;chest&gt;</code>. The bot posts publicly and auto-adds a ✅ reaction.</li>
            <li>If unclaimed after the reminder threshold, the bot sends a follow-up tagging the player again.</li>
            <li>On claim, the bot edits the message to "✅ Regear Claimed" and tags you to empty the chest.</li>
            <li>On expiry, the bot marks it "❌ Regear Expired" and tags you to empty the chest anyway.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="clock" class="tb-cmdsection">
      <div class="tb-cmdtitle"><h2>World Clock</h2><code class="tb-slashchip">/clock</code></div>
      <p class="tb-cmddesc">Creates and manages voice channels that display the current time in different time zones, updating every minute.</p>
      <p class="tb-cmd-adminreq">Administrator permission required for every /clock command.</p>

      <div class="tb-cmdcard">
        <div class="tb-cmdcard-label">COMMANDS</div>
        <div class="tb-cmdrows">
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/clock setup</code><span>Creates 3 default clocks — UTC, Eastern, Pacific. Running again deletes and replaces existing clocks (confirmation required).</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/clock add</code><span>Opens a modal for a label and IANA time zone string (e.g. <code>Europe/London</code>).</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/clock replace</code><span>Pick a clock, then enter a new label and time zone.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/clock remove</code><span>Pick a clock from the dropdown to delete its voice channel.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/clock list</code><span>Lists all configured clocks and their time zones.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="bank" class="tb-cmdsection">
      <div class="tb-cmdtitle"><h2>Bank</h2><code class="tb-slashchip">/bank</code></div>
      <p class="tb-cmddesc">Tracks player silver balances per server. Balances can go negative. All responses are visible only to whoever ran the command.</p>

      <div class="tb-cmdcard">
        <div class="tb-cmdcard-label">COMMANDS</div>
        <div class="tb-cmdrows">
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/bank_view &lt;user&gt;</code><span>Shows a player's current silver balance.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode-admin">/bank update</code><span>Admin only. Adjusts a player's balance by adding or subtracting silver.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode-admin">/bank payout &lt;user&gt;</code><span>Admin only. Resets a player's balance to zero.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode-admin">/bank debt_list</code><span>Admin only. Shows all recorded balances, highest to lowest.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="admin" class="tb-cmdsection">
      <div class="tb-cmdtitle"><h2>Admin</h2><code class="tb-slashchip">/admin</code></div>
      <p class="tb-cmddesc">Guild-wide configuration. All commands require the Administrator permission and are run once per server; responses are ephemeral.</p>

      <div class="tb-callout">Changes to reminder/expiry only apply to timers started <strong>after</strong> the change — running timers keep their original settings.</div>

      <div class="tb-cmdcard">
        <div class="tb-cmdcard-label">COMMANDS</div>
        <div class="tb-cmdrows">
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/admin set_default_tax &lt;0–100&gt;</code><span>Sets the default tax rate for loot splits — pre-fills the Calculate button. e.g. <code>35</code> means 35%.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/admin set_reminder &lt;hours&gt;</code><span>1–168h, must be less than expiry. Default: 24h.</span></div>
          <div class="tb-cmdrow"><code class="tb-cmdcode">/admin set_expiry &lt;hours&gt;</code><span>1–168h, must be greater than reminder. Default: 48h.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="permissions" class="tb-cmdsection">
      <div class="tb-cmdtitle"><h2>Permissions</h2></div>
      <p class="tb-cmddesc">By default, most commands are open to any server member. Discord's own Integrations settings let admins restrict or grant access per command, by role, user, or channel — on top of whatever the bot itself checks.</p>

      <div class="tb-infocard">
        <div class="tb-infocard-title">Getting there</div>
        <p>Server Settings → Integrations → find Tacklebox → <strong>Manage</strong>. You'll see every registered command with its own toggle — default is all members allowed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tb-flowgrid">
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-player">RESTRICT /party TO OFFICERS</div>
          <ol>
            <li>Find <strong>party</strong> in the bot's command list.</li>
            <li>Toggle off <strong>@everyone</strong>.</li>
            <li>Add roles or members → select your officer role.</li>
            <li>Toggle that role on, then save.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="tb-flowcard">
          <div class="tb-flowlabel-officer">EXPOSE /admin TO A CO-ADMIN ROLE</div>
          <ol>
            <li>Find <strong>admin</strong> in the bot's command list.</li>
            <li>Toggle off @everyone, add your trusted non-Administrator role.</li>
            <li>The bot still rejects <code>/admin</code> from anyone lacking real Administrator permission — Discord toggles and bot checks are independent layers.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</div>
